    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1244">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/372.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Decrees No. 30 and 31 dated Monterey July 20 have just been published in Tampico.
                    These decrees provide for increase in oil production tax from twenty cents
                    Mexican gold per ton to sixty cents Mexican gold per ton, or payable in New York
                    exchange at rate of two for one. Referring all recent correspondence and
                    telegrams re oil industry, this is a serious increase in taxation especially
                    taking into consideration low price crude oil in States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
